<subSubSection pageId="154" pageNumber="756" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="154.[2063,2656,1481,1904]" lastBlockId="154.[1449,2655,1910,2337]" pageId="154" pageNumber="756">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2064,2344,1713,1747]" pageId="154" pageNumber="756">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 126-169 mm, tail 124-203 mm, ear 20-24 mm, hindfoot 28-33 mm; weight 60-120 g. The West African Rock Rat, a medium-sized rat, has fur soft and medium-brown dorsally, grading to white ventrally. Ears are medium-sized and brown. Tail is relatively long (103-110% of head—body length) and scaled, brown above and paler below. Limbs are relatively short, foreand hindfeet dorsally bright yellowish-brown, with four digits on forefoot and five on hindfoot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
